The paper focuses on the performance analysis of a communication protocol (C-V2X) in vehicular networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the scheduling mechanism and resource allocation, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper uses simulations to analyze the performance, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) categories.
